    "body": "I have 50Mb, so bandwidth shouldn't be a problem. The lan light on the Pi is flashing away quite a lot, so it may be that the CPU is saturated. Anyway, I renamed the blockchain directory so it started again (as I was getting errors on the output - I can give more details if necessary).\n\nI'm using `--vmodule=downloader=6` and maxpeers at 10, verbosity 4. I've got messages about importing headers and receipts, but also repeatedly \"synchronisation already in progress\". There is only one geth instance running. Shall I ignore those errors? eth.syncing.currentblock keeps on going up, so it's making progress.\n",
